class Solution {
public:
    int trailingZeroes(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n >= 5) {
            count += n / 5;
            n /= 5;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution works by counting the number of factors of 5 in n!, as a trailing zero is formed by a 2 and a 5, and there are usually more 2s than 5s. It iteratively divides n by 5, adding the quotient to the count, until n is less than 5.

